        {
            "title": "歐元區第二季度經濟略微成長 受庫存和支出推動",
            "description": "<div class=\"atoms\"><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"587\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/9qGHlaExsdstNGpwCQPYqw--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTU4NztjZj13ZWJw/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/a7c540358ce0d42ce45d6482aee03f35\" width=\"960\"/></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><br/></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\"><span class=\"news-dateline\">【彭博】--</span> 受庫存及政府和家庭支出推動，歐元區經濟第二季度實現微弱成長。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">歐盟統計局周五公佈，歐元區第二季度GDP環比成長0.1%。這與8月中旬公佈的初值以及彭博調查分析師所得的預估一致。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">聲明稱，庫存增加為經濟成長貢獻了0.5個百分點，政府和家庭支出也提供了支持。淨貿易和投資則構成拖累。</p><figure class=\"mb-module-gap\"><div class=\"mx-auto w-fit\"><img alt=\" \" class=\"rounded-lg\" height=\"587\" src=\"https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/ip06wmlF9DdebkbJRMyDMg--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTk2MDtoPTU4NztjZj13ZWJw/https://media.zenfs.com/en/bloomberg_chinese_traditional_757/08c7940bb6974cd3305d9a40ccb719e8\" width=\"960\"/><figcaption class=\"text-px14 text-dolphin mt-2 wrap-anywhere\" style=\"max-width:960px\"> </figcaption></div></figure><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">歐洲央行幾天後就將公佈利率決定，市場普遍預計官員們將連續第二次按兵不動。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">彭博周五早些時候發布的一項調查顯示，經濟學家認為歐洲央行的降息周期已結束。就在8月中旬，他們還預計會再次降息。投資者也已不再篤定該行會再降息。</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">原文標題Euro-Zone Quarterly Growth Was Driven by Inventories, Spending</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">--聯合報導 Harumi Ichikura、Joel Rinneby、Barbara Sladkowska.</p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">More stories like this are available on <a class=\"link\" data-ylk=\"slk:bloomberg.com;elm:context_link;itc:0;sec:content-canvas\" href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">bloomberg.com</a></p><p class=\"mb-module-gap break-words leading-[1.4] text-px20 lg:text-px18 lg:leading-[1.8] text-batcave\">©2025 Bloomberg L.P.</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.news.yahoo.com/%E6%AD%90%E5%85%83%E5%8D%80%E7%AC%AC%E4%BA%8C%E5%AD%A3%E5%BA%A6%E7%B6%93%E6%BF%9F%E7%95%A5%E5%BE%AE%E6%88%90%E9%95%B7-%E5%8F%97%E5%BA%AB%E5%AD%98%E5%92%8C%E6%94%AF%E5%87%BA%E6%8E%A8%E5%8B%95-093015301.html",
